      "matters": "PETITION FOR PROBATE OF WILL AND FOR LETTERS TESTAMENTARY, Appointment Under IAEA<br>Off Calendar Apr-14-2026 Granted Per Written Order<br>MINI MINUTES: Appearances: Phillip Robb appeared via zoom for Lawrence Chu (petitioner). <br><br>\"Counsel acknowledged that Probate Code section 8226(c)(2) applies and presented oral argument that this petition was timely filed.  The Court accepted petitioner's position stated in his supplement that he first obtained knowledge of the will on January 26, 2026 when he verified the existence of the original will.\" There being no objections, the Court granted the Petition for Probate of Will and for Letters Testamentary. The will dated January 21, 2015 is admitted to probate. Laurence Chu is appointed as the Executor of the estate with full authority. Bond is not required. Order for the same signed in open Court. Status on close of estate is set for November 2,2027 at 9:00 a.m., in Dept. 204. If either a petition for final distribution, or a petition for approval of report on status on administration is filed two weeks prior to the hearing date, the status hearing will go off calendar.  <br><br>Judge:Russell S. Roeca. Clerk: A. Datt. Deputy: Fajardo. Not reported.<br>",
